quran[78]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,IT IS the Merciful
  55,2,who has taught the Koran
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,and taught him articulate speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon pursue their ordered course
  55,6,The plants and the trees bow down in adoration
  55,7,The heaven He raised on high and set the Balance of all things
  55,8,that you might not transgress that Balance
  55,9,"Give just weight and full measure, and do not cheat the Balance"
  55,10,And the earth He laid for His creatures
  55,11,with all its fruits and blossom-bearing palm
  55,12,chaff-covered grain and scented herbs
  55,13,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you² deny
  55,14,He created man from potter‘s clay
  55,15,and the jinn from smokeless fire
  55,16,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,17,"The Lord of the two easts³ is He, and the Lord of the two wests"
  55,18,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,19,"He has let loose the two seas:⁴ they meet one another"
  55,20,Yet between them stands a barrier which they cannot overrun
  55,21,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,22,Pearls and corals come out from both
  55,23,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,24,His are the ships that sail like mountains upon the ocean
  55,25,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,26,All that live on earth are doomed to die
  55,27,"But the face of your Lord will abide for ever, in all its majesty and glory"
  55,28,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,29,All who dwell in heaven and earth entreat Him. Each day some mighty task engages Him
  55,30,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,31,"Jinn and mankind, We shall surely find the time to judge you"
  55,32,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,33,"You race of jinn and mankind, if you have power to penetrate the confines of heaven and earth, then penetrate them. But this you shall not do except with Our own authority"
  55,34,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,35,"Flames of fire shall be lashed at you, and molten brass. There shall be none to help you"
  55,36,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,37,"When the sky splits asunder, and reddens like a rose or stained leather"
  55,38,so which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,39,on that day neither man nor jinnee will be asked about his sins
  55,40,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,41,The transgressors will be known by their looks; they shall be seized by their forelocks and their feet
  55,42,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,43,That is the Hell the transgressors deny
  55,44,They shall wander between fire and water fiercely seething
  55,45,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,46,But for those that fear the majesty of their Lord there are two Gardens
  55,47,so which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,48,planted with shady trees
  55,49,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,50,Each is watered by a flowing spring
  55,51,Which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,52,Each bears every kind of fruit in pairs
  55,53,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,54,"They shall recline on couches lined with rich brocade, and within reach will hang the fruits of both Gardens"
  55,55,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,56,Therein are bashful virgins whom neither man nor jinnee will have touched before
  55,57,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,58,Virgins as fair as corals and rubies
  55,59,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,60,Shall the reward of goodness be anything but good
  55,61,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,62,And beside these there shall be two other Gardens
  55,63,so which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,64,of darkest green
  55,65,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,66,A gushing fountain shall flow in each
  55,67,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,68,"Each planted with fruit-trees, the palm and the pomegranate"
  55,69,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,70,In each there shall be virgins chaste and fair
  55,71,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,72,"Dark-eyed virgins, sheltered in their tents"
  55,73,so which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,74,whom neither man nor jinnee will have touched before
  55,75,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,76,They shall recline on green cushions and fine carpets
  55,77,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,78,"Blessed be the name of your Lord, the Lord of Majesty and Glory"